sparql_query_kg2:
Based on the provided information, I will create a SPARQL query for KG2 (Wikidata) to match the original query in KG1 (DBpedia).

The original DBpedia query is:
```
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX res: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?uri
WHERE { 
  ?x dbo:director res:William_Shatner ;
  dbo:starring ?uri 
}
```
The corresponding Wikidata query is:
```
PREFIX wdt: <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/direct/>
PREFIX wd: <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?uri
WHERE { 
  ?x wdt:P57 wd:Q16297 ; 
  wdt:P161 ?uri 
}
```
However, we need to map the DBpedia IDs to Wikidata IDs using the ER2 mapping:
```
[
  {
    "dbpedia_id": "http://dbpedia.org/ontology/director",
    "wikidata_ids": [
      "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/P57"
    ]
  },
  {
    "dbpedia_id": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Shatner",
    "wikidata_ids": [
      "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q16297"
    ]
  },
  {
    "dbpedia_id": "http://dbpedia.org/ontology/starring",
    "wikidata_ids": [
      "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/P161"
    ]
  }
]
```
Using this mapping, we can replace the DBpedia IDs with the corresponding Wikidata IDs:
```
PREFIX wdt: <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/direct/>
PREFIX wd: <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?uri
WHERE { 
  ?x wdt:P57 wd:Q16297 ; 
  wdt:P161 ?uri 
}
```
This is already the final query. However, I can format it within the required tags for clarity.

<sparql>
PREFIX wdt: <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/direct/>
PREFIX wd: <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?uri
WHERE { 
  ?x wdt:P57 wd:Q16297 ; 
  wdt:P161 ?uri 
}
</sparql>

This query will return the Wikidata URIs of actors starring in movies directed by William Shatner.

