sparql_query_kg2:
To produce a SPARQL query for KG2, we need to map the DBpedia IDs to Wikidata IDs and use the corresponding Wikidata property URIs. 

First, let's examine the ER2 mapping:
[  
  {  
    "dbpedia_id": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Three_Dancers",  
    "wikidata_ids": [  
      "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q3235867"  
    ]  
  },  
  {  
    "dbpedia_id": "http://dbpedia.org/ontology/author",  
    "wikidata_ids": [  
      "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/P50"  
    ]  
  },  
  {  
    "dbpedia_id": "http://dbpedia.org/ontology/movement",  
    "wikidata_ids": [  
      "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/P135"  
    ]  
  }  
]

We need to map the DBpedia ID for "The Three Dancers" to its corresponding Wikidata ID, which is Q3235867. We also need to map the DBpedia property "author" to its corresponding Wikidata property, which is P50. Finally, we need to map the DBpedia property "movement" to its corresponding Wikidata property, which is P135.

Now, let's construct the SPARQL query for KG2:

<sparql>
PREFIX wdt: <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/direct/> 
PREFIX wd: <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/> 
SELECT DISTINCT ?uri 
WHERE { 
  wd:Q3235867 wdt:P50 ?person . 
  ?person wdt:P135 ?uri 
}
</sparql>

This query will return the artistic movement to which the painter of "The Three Dancers" belongs.

